=======
Changes
=======

1.0.0 (2025-10-12)
==================

**Production Release - API Stable**

This is the first stable release of rut. The API is now considered stable
and will follow semantic versioning.

New Features
------------

- Add ``--version`` flag to display version information
- Comprehensive type hints added to all public APIs
- Detailed docstrings for all public classes and methods
- Improved error messages for invalid async test configurations

Improvements
------------

- Better CLI help text with examples and repository link
- Enhanced warning filter validation with clearer error messages
- More robust conftest.py loading with better error handling
- Improved documentation throughout the codebase

Changes
-------

- Version bumped to 1.0.0 to signal production readiness
- Development status updated to "Production/Stable" in package metadata
- Enhanced package classifiers for better discoverability

0.3.0 (*unreleased*)
====================

- Colorized test output using ``rich``.

0.2.1 (2025-07-06)
====================

- Fix: Add README to PyPI package description.

0.2.0 (2025-07-06)
====================

- Project revived, requires Python 3.12+ (3.13 supported)
- Test discovery and filtering by keyword (`-k`)
- Exit on first failure (`-x`)
- Disable output capturing (`-s`)
- Code coverage (`--cov`)
- Sort tests by their definition order
- Async test validation
- Warning collection and reporting
- Improved CLI with proper exit codes and conditional `ipdb` support
- Set `TEST_RUNNER=rut` environment variable
- Coverage source is now configurable via `pyproject.toml` and defaults to `["src", "tests"]`
- Warning filters are now configurable via `pyproject.toml`
- Session-level setup and teardown hooks (`rut_session_setup`, `rut_session_teardown`) in `conftest.py`

0.1.0 (*2022-04-29*)
====================

- minimal test runner